@flexiarg coordination/mandatory-psr
@title Mandatory PSR (G3)
@keywords psr, pattern, selection, gap, obligation
@audience coordination maintainers, futon3b builders
@tone formal-analytic
@references [futon-theory/proof-path futon-theory/stop-the-line]

! conclusion:
  If you want execution to be pattern-governed rather than post-hoc rationalized, require a Pattern Selection Record (PSR) before execution, or a typed gap declaration.

  + context: Pattern use must be chosen before acting, not retroactively claimed.
  + IF:
    you want work to be guided by shared patterns and constraints

  + HOWEVER:
    letting execution proceed without PSR makes validation ambiguous and invites confabulated explanations

  + THEN:
    require PSR (pattern selected) or Gap PSR (pattern missing) at G3 before G2 can run

  + BECAUSE:
    this makes the pipeline auditable: you can compare chosen pattern vs outcome later

